description = Retrieve, capture, or refresh distilled evaluation-observability knowledge — measuring and observing LLM and agent systems: eval-driven development, error analysis, building eval datasets, LLM-as-judge and aligning it to humans, code vs model-graded evals, eval harnesses and CI, online vs offline eval, tracing and spans, production monitoring and drift, and agent-trajectory and RAG evaluation. Use when deciding what and how to measure an agent's quality, building an eval suite or a judge, instrumenting traces, or looking up or saving an evaluation concept — not when enforcing I/O validation or injection defenses at runtime (that is guardrails-safety-security), nor when implementing the runtime that acts on a trace such as retries or kill-switches (that is agent-runtime).
